title: Deceptive Statistics: Does the law treat all individuals equally?
description: Created two different graphs which argue both sides of the substantiated complaints in New York. One side argues that all races' complains are justified, the other argues that black individuals are treated more unfairly.

title: Off Target: Your Average Carton of Eggs Costs An Additional $4.69
description: Analyzed the change in price between 2022 and the present egg prices from Target, which rose significantly across most brands, sizes, and types. The rise in price may be due to factors like inflation over time and the avian influenza.

title: How Long Will It Take? Predicting Recipe Duration
description: Conducted statistical analysis and data cleaning from a dataset of over 83,000 recipes and built multiple regression models to predict recipe duration using features found in meta data like ingredients, steps, and user ratings.

title: Draw & Detect: Real-Time Handwriting Classifier
description: Developed an interactive (K-NN) classifier to predict digits drawn by users, with real-time digit recognition through an interactive drawing interface that allowed users to sketch digits, which classified numbers using the Euclidean distance metric.

title: Self-Run Neighborhood Battery Recycling Collection Program
description: Prioritized elderly and nursing home residents who did not have easy access to safe deposit locations, averaging 40 pounds of batteries per week, keeping harmful acids and battery chemicals from releasing, polluting, and harming the environment.

title: Cultural Exchange Ambassador and English Teacher
description: Created a fun online learning experience for elementary schoolers in China & Taiwan, developed teaching aids for interactive oral and grammar lessons.

title: Roseville Urban Forest Foundation (RUFF) Pre-Planting Program
description: Researched and created a poster that is displayed at all planting events. Contains information about native trees to inform volunteers about the trees that they are planting.

title: Paw-Dentify: Recognizing Your Furry Friend
description: Developed a machine learning model in Microsoft Azure, trained and fine-tuned a model to accurately recognize and categorize pets from user-submitted images, utilizing advanced techniques and skills obtained from the tutorship of Francesca Lazzeri at Columbia University.
